|12,73
     The "StrDelete" procedure deletes a number of characters from a
string.  The first argument of StrDelete is a string variable.  The second
is an integer, giving the number of characters to be deleted.  The third
is another integer, giving the subscript of the first character to be
deleted.

StrDelete Examples:
     str := 'Hixxxx there!';
     StrDelete(str,4,3);
     writeln(str);
         {Will write out "Hi there!"}
